## Description {#details}

Used for dynamically loading instances of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/inlineorder">InlineOrder</a> as plugins.

Plugins must implement an <a href="#a6f63aac075f4dbf0570c39aa982d1daf">InlineOrderFactory</a>, for an example refer to: llvm/unittests/Analysis/InlineOrderPlugin/InlineOrderPlugin.cpp

If a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/plugininlineorderanalysis">PluginInlineOrderAnalysis</a> has been registered with the current <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#af9c9208365fd9ce11392b4d79485e259">ModuleAnalysisManager</a>, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a7acaa9d2987b3c0842cc1a758bfcb0d0">llvm::getInlineOrder</a> returns an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/inlineorder">InlineOrder</a> created by the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/plugininlineorderanalysis">PluginInlineOrderAnalysis</a>&#39; Factory.

Definition at line 51 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/inlineorder-h">InlineOrder.h</a>.
